<Layout title="Farcaster - Antarctica DAO">
	<h1>Farcaster: Decentralized Social Media</h1>
	
	<section>
		<h2>What is Farcaster?</h2>
		<p>Farcaster is a sufficiently decentralized social network built on Ethereum. It aims to create an open protocol for public conversations, enabling users to own their identities and data while fostering a vibrant ecosystem of interoperable clients.</p>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Key Features</h2>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Decentralized Identity:</strong> Users own their identities through Ethereum addresses.</li>
			<li><strong>Open Protocol:</strong> Anyone can build clients and applications on top of Farcaster.</li>
			<li><strong>Data Portability:</strong> Users can easily move their data between different clients.</li>
			<li><strong>Censorship Resistance:</strong> No single entity controls the network or user data.</li>
			<li><strong>Interoperability:</strong> Farcaster can integrate with other Web3 protocols and applications.</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>How Farcaster Works</h2>
		<p>Farcaster uses a hybrid architecture that combines on-chain and off-chain components:</p>
		<ol>
			<li><strong>On-chain Registry:</strong> Ethereum smart contracts manage user identities and basic account information.</li>
			<li><strong>Off-chain Data Storage:</strong> Content (casts, reactions, etc.) is stored off-chain for scalability and cost-efficiency.</li>
			<li><strong>Hubs:</strong> Decentralized nodes that store and serve user data.</li>
			<li><strong>Clients:</strong> Applications that interact with the Farcaster protocol, allowing users to create and consume content.</li>
		</ol>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Why Support Farcaster?</h2>
		<p>Antarctica DAO believes in Farcaster's vision of a decentralized social media landscape. By supporting Farcaster, we aim to:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Promote user sovereignty and data ownership</li>
			<li>Foster innovation in decentralized communication</li>
			<li>Create a more open and transparent social media ecosystem</li>
			<li>Empower developers to build the next generation of social applications</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section>
		<h2>Get Involved</h2>
		<p>Interested in contributing to the Farcaster ecosystem? Here's how you can get started:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Explore the <a href="https://www.farcaster.xyz/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Farcaster website</a> and documentation</li>
			<li>Join the Farcaster community on Discord</li>
			<li>Contribute to open-source Farcaster projects on GitHub</li>
			<li>Apply for grants through Antarctica DAO to build on Farcaster</li>
		</ul>
	</section>
</Layout>

